&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter&quot; src=&quot;http://cdn.makeuseof.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/JC-Penny-SmartThings.png?x16845&quot; alt=&quot;JC Penny Black Friday SmartThings&quot; width=&quot;408&quot; height=&quot;408&quot;/&gt;Image Credit: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.jcpenney.com/p/samsung-smartthings-home-monitoring-kit/ppr5007221594&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;JC Penney&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Protecting your home is vital. Where once home security systems were expensive and cumbersome, now they’re deceptively simple to set up. Among the top choices, the SmartThings home monitoring kit is an excellent value. For Black Friday, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theblackfriday.com/jcpenney-blackfriday.shtml?page=7&quot;&gt;JC Penney lowers the price to $150&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter&quot; src=&quot;http://cdn.makeuseof.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/oculus-rift.jpg?x16845&quot; alt=&quot;oculus rift black friday&quot; width=&quot;636&quot; height=&quot;386&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;In summer of 2017, the Oculus Rift (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/oculus-rift-review-giveaway/&quot;&gt;our Oculus review&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;link-callout&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;link-callout-image&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;link-callout-image-container&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/oculus-rift-review-giveaway/&quot; onclick=&quot;ga('send','event','ui','link-callout');&quot;&gt;Oculus Rift Review&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;link-callout-info&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;link-callout-title&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/oculus-rift-review-giveaway/&quot; onclick=&quot;ga('send','event','ui','link-callout');&quot;&gt;Oculus Rift Review&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;link-callout-excerpt&quot;&gt;Virtual Reality is not new, but it's finally affordable and within our grasp. After four year and two development prototypes, the final consumer edition of the Oculus Rift has arrived.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/oculus-rift-review-giveaway/&quot; class=&quot;link-callout-link&quot; onclick=&quot;ga('send','event','ui','link-callout');&quot;&gt;Read More&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; ) saw a &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/oculus-rift-bundle-alternatives/&quot;&gt;discount to $400&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;link-callout&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;link-callout-image&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;link-callout-image-container&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/oculus-rift-bundle-alternatives/&quot; onclick=&quot;ga('send','event','ui','link-callout');&quot;&gt;Is the Discounted $400 Oculus Rift Bundle Worth Buying? 7 Alternatives&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;link-callout-info&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;link-callout-title&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/oculus-rift-bundle-alternatives/&quot; onclick=&quot;ga('send','event','ui','link-callout');&quot;&gt;Is the Discounted $400 Oculus Rift Bundle Worth Buying? 7 Alternatives&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;link-callout-excerpt&quot;&gt;Getting started with virtual reality costs a lot. Fortunately, the VR headset Oculus Rift (and its Touch controllers) just dropped to $399. It might be a good time to try VR.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/oculus-rift-bundle-alternatives/&quot; class=&quot;link-callout-link&quot; onclick=&quot;ga('send','event','ui','link-callout');&quot;&gt;Read More&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; . For Black Friday, the Rift gets an all-time low $350 package. It’s the best deal yet on a VR headset. However, you’ll want to consider upgrading your rig if you’re going in on an Oculus. Since its $400 bundle was a supreme value, the $350 is a must-have for anyone keen on virtual reality gaming.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Want to make a gaming upgrade for a bit less? Check out the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.bestbuy.com/site/sony-playstation4-1tb-console-black/5850905.p?skuId=5850905&quot;&gt;PlayStation 4 1 TB console&lt;/a&gt; for $199, also at Best Buy. This shouldn’t require any upgrades aside from purchasing games, unless you don’t have a television or monitor.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Gaming isn’t merely about having the best graphics card. An amazing GPU is lacking without an equally as incredible display. Dell’s S2716DG plummets in price to a mere $400. This 27-inch monitor might not be an ultrawide panel, but it’s a stunning monitor with a 144 Hz refresh rate, HDMI 1.4, DisplayPort 1.2, and four USB 3.0 ports. Onboard, there’s Nvidia G-Sync and a QHD resolution for lush detail.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter&quot; src=&quot;http://cdn.makeuseof.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Mavic_Flying_Props_3-670x447.jpg?x16845&quot; alt=&quot;mavic aerial camera bundle black friday&quot; width=&quot;670&quot; height=&quot;447&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;When it comes to drones, the DJI Mavic Pro is among the best available. And come Black Friday, Costco will chop off $100 of its price. At $900, you get a DJI Mavic Pro drone, aerial camera, controller, battery charger, backpack, propeller guards, and a 16GB microSD card. It’s capable of shooting 4K video at 30 frames per second. If you’re in the market for a drone, this is the package to snag.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
